hod is used to determine the\nintrinsic scatter in Mbh, our dataset shows weak evidence for increased scatter\nat Mbulge < 10^{11} Msun or L_V < 10^{10.3} Lsun, while the scatter stays\nconstant for 10^{11} < Mbulge < 10^{12.3} Msun and 10^{10.3} < L_V < 10^{11.5}\nLsun. A Bayesian analysis indicates a larger sample of Mbh measurements would\nbe needed to detect any statistically significant trend in the scatter with\ngalaxy properties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Nov 2012 21:00:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 14 Nov 2012 01:19:33 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 9 Jan 2013 05:46:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
